    "description": "An Early Byzantine fortified settlement in the Liguria Maritima.",
    "details": "<p>A hilltop settlement, with occupation in the Late Bronze Age, was then abandoned and rebuilt as a fortress during the Byzantine rule of Liguria (mid-6th to mid-7th CE). It is slightly inland, probably meant more as a watchtower against military actions from the North, as is the case for Filattiera, further East.</p>\r\n<p>In the Middle Ages, a church was built on the hilltop site.</p>",
